The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Russia signs 19 deals
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                      Russia signs 19 deals
                            
	New Delhi, March 12 (PTI): India and Russia today signed 19 deals, including the revised agreement on the Gorshkov aircraft carrier and one to build 12 atomic plants.        
	Six of Russias 12 atomic plants will be in Tamil Nadus Kudankulam, the rest in Haripur in Bengal.        
	The agreements were signed during the visit of Russian Prime Minister Vladimir Putin who held talks with his counterpart Manmohan Singh.         
	The two leaders discussed regional issues, including Afghanistan and Pakistan in the context of terrorism, and agreed to intensify their consultations on Afghanistan  the challenges posed by terrorism and extremism in the region.        
	 The Gorshkov deal was signed in 2004 at the cost of $1.5 billion, along with 16 MiG-29Ks. However, the Russians later demanded $2.9 billion, citing escalation of costs.        
	 After protracted negotiations, the two sides settled at $2.34 billion.                                                                                                                                                           
